'''Tour Aryon''' was the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who served as [[Governor/Legends|governor]] of the [[Desert/Legends|desert]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] under the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. She was a [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] from [[Treylon II]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|The capitol has been very active recently with the news of the new election. I have a new project that I'm heading and have chosen two eligible candidates to work with me. However, to avoid the show of unfair favoritism, I have left it to the people of Bestine to select the politician who best represents them.|Tour Aryon|<ref name="Galaxies">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>}}

Tour Aryon was born on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Treylon II]]. She met and married her husband, [[Kant Aryon|Kant]], the son of a wealthy [[Baron/Legends|baron]] and [[Baroness/Legends|baroness]]. He was a [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]] who moved in underworld circles, but recanted the life so as not to jeopardize Aryon's [[Politics/Legends|political]] career when she was appointed as [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine's]] [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Governor/Legends|governor]]. Upon her arrival, Aryon moved her offices into a palatial house located in [[Bestine (city)/Legends|Bestine]], and immediately appointed [[Orun Depp]] as [[Imperial Prefect]]. She placed him in charge of running Tatooine's [[Standard day/Legends|day]]-to-day affairs.<ref name="GG7" />

Aryon's contributions to Tatooine focused on the cultural, much of which was lost on the average Tatooinian. She established a [[Museum/Legends|museum]] in Bestine, which boasted the only complete [[Krayt dragon/Legends|Krayt dragon]] skeleton on the planet, and hosted lavish garden parties with expensive, imported entertainment. Aryon did not respect the citizens of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], considering them to be peasants and savages.<ref name="GG7" /> The governor maintained an [[Agent/Legends|agent]] in the [[City/Legends|city]] who reported directly to her who was known as "[[Sariss|Prophetess]]."<ref name="CCG-Prophetess">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=Prophetess}}</ref>

When [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] sent his own [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] to the surface of Tatooine to [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|search]] for [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], Tour objected, insisting that her own [[Soldier/Legends|troops]] could handle it. When Vader was informed of her objections, he did not care.<ref name="ANH">''[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novel]]''</ref> After [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Prefect/Legends|Prefect]] [[Orun Depp]] was assassinated by the [[Assassin droid/Legends|assassin droid]] [[IG-72]], [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] Tour replaced him with [[Eugene Talmont]].<ref name="GG7" />

==Personality and traits==
Tour Aryon was sharp and quick-witted, capable of analyzing a situation quickly and then reacting appropriately. Despite her slight appearance, the governor projected an imposing presence. She often took on the air of a [[General/Legends|general]] when inspecting her [[Soldier/Legends|troops]]. Ayron wore fashionable [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]] and spent her time throwing parties and entertaining guests. Her objective was to keep Tatooine quiet and peaceful, which would allow her to secure a promotion and a relocation away from the planet.<ref name="GG7" />

The term "tourist" entered [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley's]] local slang meaning "a person was unable to get anything done." It was in reference to Governor Aryon's inability to actually accomplish anything, and its usage was deliberately confusing to visitors to the settlement.<ref name="GG7" />

==Behind the scenes==
The scenes where Imperial [[Chief/Legends|Chief]] [[Moradmin Bast/Legends|Moradmin Bast]] and Vader discussed Aryon's objections were cut from the final film of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']], but were used for ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'', albeit with altered dialogue in which Vader and a [[Unidentified Moradmin Bast look-alike|Bast look-alike]] discussed finding [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] on [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]].

